    "Intake, command and externally retried POST operations normally require idempotency.",
    "Idempotency keys are scoped by tenant, actor/service identity, route and operation.",
    "A key may not be reused with a different request fingerprint.",
    "A matching replay returns the original committed result where safe.",
    "An in-progress replay returns a stable conflict/in-progress response.",
    "Failed operations must declare whether the key is reusable.",
    "LINK delivery identifiers do not replace business-command idempotency keys.",
    "Database transaction IDs are internal and not public idempotency keys.",
    "Secrets must not be embedded in idempotency keys.",
    "Idempotency storage implementation is outside this task.",
    "Legacy operations may enter compatibility mode but must remain explicitly classified."
